1
00:00:04,700 --> 00:00:08,700
Trials are usually imported, but you can also create new trials within the KDSmart app. 

2
00:00:09,633 --> 00:00:13,633
Go to the Trials screen and choose the Create Trial option from the Menu.

3
00:00:18,166 --> 00:00:22,166
Enter the details such as the trial name

4
00:00:28,266 --> 00:00:32,266
Here we are creating an X/Y trial with columns and rows and each plot has an x/y coordinate. We will demontrate Plot trials later in the video.

5
00:00:34,100 --> 00:00:38,100
For X/Y trials, you need to choose the number of columns and the number of rows.

6
00:00:44,266 --> 00:00:48,266
Optionally, you can add a number of subplots.

7
00:00:48,633 --> 00:00:52,633
Choosing '2' here means that each plot in the trial will contain two subplots.

8
00:00:55,033 --> 00:00:59,033
Choose a trait instance style to determine how instances of the same trait are shown.

9
00:01:01,133 --> 00:01:05,133
Select the Confirm button when you are ready to create the trial. 

10
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:10,033
It will now appear on the Trials screen and you can select it to add more details.

11
00:01:11,766 --> 00:01:15,766
Select the Edit button for traits to add traits to the trial.

12
00:01:31,333 --> 00:01:35,333
Add trait instances if you want to score the same trait multiple times.

13
00:01:49,966 --> 00:01:53,966
Now we are going to create a Plot ID trial.

14
00:01:59,266 --> 00:02:03,266
Plot ID trials contains plots with unique identification numbers.

15
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:11,600
Choose the number of plots you want in the trial.

16
00:02:13,766 --> 00:02:17,766
The Run Length can be set to vertical or horizontal.

17
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:31,400
No subplots were added to the Plot ID trial.

18
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:35,400
Select the Add Subplot option from the Menu if you want to add them later.
